&lt;p&gt;Staff Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wolf ward are keen to welcome the final member of their ward nursing team!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wolf have a friendly team of both experienced and new nurses. We specialise in Colorectal, Hepatobiliary surgery &amp; Oesophageal-Gastric for planned and emergency patients. We offer the opportunity to gain experience in the two higher dependency level 1 areas that are located centrally on the ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pledge to support you through a robust training programme tailored to your individual needs &amp; interests.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a dedicated surgical clinical educator and a large team of sisters ready to buddy up with you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We advise any interested applicants to pop in and have an informal walk around the area to meet Sister &amp; chat with our friendly team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Senior Sister Sue Mallinson on &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;susan.mallinson1&lt;/span&gt;@nhs.net or (01752) 439677&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
